{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3e3ea7c5-7c08-4d19-915e-208bcbfd5948","content":"On macOS, the system crash reporter automatically generates `.ips` crash logs when any process crashes. No special setup needed.\n\n**Find your crash report here:**\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\n\nLook for a `.ips` file matching your process name and crash timestamp.\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n\n**For a traditional core dump**, run this *before* launching your app:\n\n```bash\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\nCore dumps land in `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\n---\n\nOnce you have the `.ips` file, I can help you **symbolicate** the .NET runtime frames to map native addresses back to source code — just invoke the `apple-crash-symbolication` skill.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9de84cb-5525-4eb9-9b98-9236430ed965","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a diagnostics question. Let me check if any of my available skills are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - This is about symbolicating Apple crash logs (.ips files), which is related but not exactly what they're asking.\n- `dump-collect` - This is about configuring and collecting crash dumps for .NET applications.\n\nThe `dump-collect` skill says \"USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump.\"\n\n\nBut the user is asking about finding existing crash reports after a crash has already occurred, not setting up collection beforehand. The `apple-crash-symbolication` skill covers macOS crash logs too, so I can use that to help. On macOS, the system automatically generates `.ips` crash reports when an app crashes, and they're stored in standard locations like `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` for user-level crashes and `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` for system-level ones.\n\nFor NativeAOT applications specifically, `createdump` isn't included by default, so you'd rely on the macOS crash reporter instead. You can also enable core dumps with `ulimit -c unlimited` if you want more detailed debugging information.","outputTokens":580,"requestId":"2048:69BE5:6EF3FF:817851:69F01193"},"id":"17380ed1-e833-45ac-9592-8d53e8e51fbf","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:47:17.984Z","parentId":"56883ac7-10ce-4170-86e1-5dc1d2a21d55"}
